{% block title %}{{ model.title }} : {{ global.site_title }}{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<section class="col-24">
	<h1>{{ model.title }}</h1>
</section>

<section class="col-24">
	<section class="col-8 first">

		<div class="js-mul-tabs-example mul-tabs">
			{% include "page-tabs" %}
			<div id="tabs-1">
				<p>
					A Stacked Form is a form where the Form Label is stacked on top of the Form Field. 

				<p>The stacked form is comprised of two main elements:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Form label</li>
					<li>Form field</li>
				</ul>

				<p>In this use the form label is "stacked" on top of the form field.</p>
				<p><small>**Not all form layouts will work well together</small></p>
			</div>
			<div id="tabs-2">
				<p>Stacked Forms are typically a default layout for forms.</p>

				<p>Stacked Forms are best used when a high level of end-user configurability is necessary. In cases like this, we have less control over the specific placement of all fields, so the flexibility of spacing is important. 
				</p>
				
				<p>
				The Stacked Form is flexible because it allows you to configure optional elements: 
				</p>
				
				<ul>
					<li>Hiding/displaying Fields</li>
					<li>Changing the values of Field Labels</li>
					<li>Localization/translation of Field Labels</li>
				</ul>

				<p>The Stacked Form works well when you want the user to read a Label and take an action directly underneath. However, for aesthetic purposes, it might be a good idea to use one of the other types of Forms if its contents are on the long side.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div id="tabs-3">
		
				<h5>Margins</h5>
				<p>In order to keep with Mercer consistency, the margins between Elements have been standardized:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Use a 10 pixel bottom between the Element and next Field Label. </li>
					<li>Use a 3 pixel bottom margin between a Label and an Input.</li>
				</ul>
				
				<h5>Labels</h5>
				<p>All field labels should use Title Case. See the <a href="nar-copy-text-styleguide">Copy/Text Style Guide narrative</a> for more detail.</p>

				<h5>Active State</h5>
				<p>The active state for any field should be indicated by the application of the "Attention" color to the border of the specific field the user has clicked into.</p>
				
				<h5>Required Fields</h5>
				<p>All required fields should be denoted by placing the  Required icon (the "asterisk-required.png" image from the <a href="icons">list of icons</a>) immediately to the left of the Field Label.</p>

				<h5>Error Handling</h5>
				<p>See the <a href="form-error-message">Field Specific Error Message</a> page for details.</p>
			</div>
			<div id="tabs-4">
				<h5>Placeholder Text</h5>
				<p>Some Form Fields contain Placeholder Text. However, IE9 doesn't understand the polyfill needed to create this type of text. In this case, you will need Java Script to put the Placeholder Text where it needs to go.</p>
			</div>
		</div>

	</section>
	<section class="col-16">
		<h4 class="mul-hdr-rule">Example</h4>

		<div class="col-24">
			<div class="col-10 first">

				<!-- STACKED FORM - EXAMPLE - BEGINS -->
				<form class="mul-form" id="" name="" method="" action="" title="">
					<fieldset>
						<ol>
							<li>
								<label class="mul-required" for="">Basic Text Input:</label>
								<input class="" id="" name="" value="" tabindex="" type="text" title="" />
								<small class="mul-info">This is form info text.</small>
							</li>
							<li>
								<label class="mul-required" for="">Label:</label>
								<select id="" tabindex="">
									<option selected="selected" value="Select an item">choose one...</option>
									<option>One</option>
									<option>Two</option>
									<option>Three</option>
								</select>
								<small class="mul-info">This is form info text.</small>
							</li>

							<li>
								<label class="mul-required" for="">Label Posed as a Question?</label>
								<div class="mul-radio">
									<label for="question1" class="mul-form-inline-element">
										<input name="question" type="radio" id="question1"> Yes
									</label>

									<label for="question2" class="mul-form-inline-element">
										<input name="question" type="radio" id="question2"> No
									</label>
								</div>
								<small class="mul-info">This is form info text.</small>
							</li>

							<li>
								<label class="mul-required" for="">Year of Original Appointment:</label>
								<div class="mul-checkbox">
									<label for="2009" class="mul-form-inline-element">
										<input name="" type="checkbox" id="2009"> 2009
									</label>

									<label for="2010" class="mul-form-inline-element">
										<input name="" type="checkbox" id="2010"> 2010
									</label>

									<label for="2011" class="mul-form-inline-element">
										<input name="" type="checkbox" id="2011"> 2011
									</label>

									<label for="2012" class="mul-form-inline-element">
										<input name="" type="checkbox" id="2012"> 2012
									</label>
								</div>
								<small class="mul-info">This is form info text.</small>
							</li>
							<li>
								<label class="mul-required" for="">Comments:</label>
								<textarea></textarea>
								<small class="mul-info">This is form info text.</small>
							</li>
							<li class="mul-form-inline">
								<label  class="mul-required" for="mul-datepicker-input-from">Label:</label>
								<div class="col-24 mul-datepicker-range">
									<label class="mul-datepicker-range-sublabel-from" for="js-mul-datepicker-range-stacked-labels-from">From</label>
									<input class="col-8 mul-datepicker-range-input" id="js-mul-datepicker-range-stacked-labels-from" readonly="true" name="" value="" tabindex="" type="text" title="Select date." data-mul-datepicker-message-label="This is a calendar message area for user messages related to dates" />
									<label class="mul-datepicker-range-sublabel-to" for="js-mul-datepicker-range-stacked-labels-to">to</label>
									<input class="col-8 mul-datepicker-range-input" id="js-mul-datepicker-range-stacked-labels-to" readonly="true" name="" value="" tabindex="" type="text" title="Select date." data-mul-datepicker-message-label="This is a calendar message area for user messages related to dates" />
								</div>
								<small class="mul-info">This is form info text.</small>
							</li>

							<li class="mul-form-action"></li>
						</ol>
					</fieldset>
				</form>
				<!-- STACKED FORM - EXAMPLE - ENDS -->

			</div>
		</div>

